        <headline>Flood Advisory issued July 8 at 3:57PM CDT until July 8 at 6:00PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...A portion of northeast Illinois, including the following
counties, Cook and Will.

* WHEN...Until 600 PM CDT.

* IMPACTS...Underpasses may be flooded. Roads and streets may be
flooded.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 357 PM CDT, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges
indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Up to 2 inches of
rain have fallen near Joliet, New Lenox and Homer Glen.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Bolingbrook, Orland Park, Tinley Park, Romeoville, Woodridge,
Lockport, New Lenox, Homer Glen, Palos Hills, Lemont, Palos
Heights, Worth, Orland Hills, Palos Park and Fairmont.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>A Flood Advisory means minor flooding along waterways and other poor
drainage areas is imminent or may already be occurring. Persons in
the advisory area should use caution and avoid flood waters.</instruction>
